AssignedTask.Name: A Celebrity Visit
AssignedTask.Description: One of the most famous Mivoni bards is passing through a region of the barony. Such a chance should not be missed!

AssignedTask.Name: Fey Magic
AssignedTask.Description: A fey magician visited a settlement, and made everyday things come to life! The people seem to be more frightened than amused by the minor and generally harmless anomaly.

AssignedTask.Name: The Howling Wolves
AssignedTask.Description: Wolves are breeding at a surprising rate. The local forests are full of the ravenous beasts, and there's not enough quarry to feed them all. The starving wolves howl at night, to gather into packs and attack the villages.

AssignedTask.Name: Trade Agreement with Surtova
AssignedTask.Description: Our merchants will receive the right to establish a sizeable trading post in the heart of New Stetven. Each city in the barony gains an extra +5 BP per week; +2 BP for each Town; and +1 BP for each village.

AssignedTask.Name: Mysterious Cult
AssignedTask.Description: A mysterious cult, promoting idleness and debauchery, has emerged in the region. This depravation must be stopped!

AssignedTask.Name: An Amazing Discovery
AssignedTask.Description: Some foreign treasure hunters found an amazing artifact at a dig site. It would be nice to obtain it, but how?

ActiveTasks.Name: Pillage the Temple of the Elk
ActiveTasks.Description: Plunder the Temple of the Elk and rob it of all remaining treasure. +150 BP. Prevents future restoration of the Temple.

ActiveTasks.Name: Research into the Nature of Curses: the Scythe Tree
ActiveTasks.Description: The Scythe Tree came about as the result of a curse. Perhaps by studying what's left of it we might learn something...

ActiveTasks.Name: Research into the Nature of Curses: the Scythe Tree
ActiveTasks.Description: The Scythe Tree came about as the result of a curse. Perhaps by studying what's left of it we might learn something...

ActiveTasks.Name: Pillage the Temple of the Elk
ActiveTasks.Description: Plunder the Temple of the Elk and rob it of all remaining treasure. +150 BP. Prevents future restoration of the Temple.

ActiveTasks.Name: Research into the Nature of Curses: Tartuk
ActiveTasks.Description: Tartuccio's transformation into the kobold shaman Tartuk was truly remarkable. Could it have been the result of a curse?

ActiveTasks.Name: Research into the Nature of Curses: Candlemere
ActiveTasks.Description: The villagers believe that the lake is cursed. Or the island in the center of it is, at least. Or, at the very least, the tower on the island. — Surely, if nothing else, the tower must be cursed...

ActiveTasks.Name: Heeding to the Poor and Weak
ActiveTasks.Description: Paying attention to the community and heeding every call of distress, the Regent resolves problems with a +1 bonus.

ActiveTasks.Name: Support the Regent's Endeavors
ActiveTasks.Description: Spend two weeks resolving population problems in the barony.

ActiveTasks.Name: Support the High Priest's Endeavors
ActiveTasks.Description: Spend two weeks resolving religious problems in the barony.

ActiveTasks.Name: Border Training Camps
ActiveTasks.Description: Military camps at the border allow for immediate solutions to military problems. Provides the General a +2 bonus when resolving problems.

ActiveTasks.Name: Land Defenders
ActiveTasks.Description: +1 morale bonus to attack and damage rolls while fighting within claimed regions.

ActiveTasks.Name: Support the General's Endeavors
ActiveTasks.Description: Spend two weeks resolving the barony's military difficulties.

ActiveTasks.Name: Support the Councilor's Endeavors
ActiveTasks.Description: Spend two weeks resolving the loyalty of citizens in the barony.

ActiveTasks.Name: Local Plague
ActiveTasks.Description: The strange disease keeps spreading, claiming new lives and bringing forth new monsters. Panic is rising in the region.
